24
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,200
It's not relevant.

25
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,200
How much did you pay for it?

26
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,200
Not relevant.

27
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,200
You paid for it?

28
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,000
It all happened so fast.

29
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,480
I broke up with Karen after the job interview.

30
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:05,280
And it was a little awkward when she came back from the city.

31
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:08,720
She told me very clearly that just because we were broken up didn't mean that she was

32
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:13,440
going anywhere because she had worked really hard for her career, but the next day her

33
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:16,000
desk was empty.

34
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:23,480
And as for me and my current romantic life, I'm single now and looking.

35
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:27,080
So if you know anybody.

36
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,400
Jim and I went to dinner a few times when he got back from New York.

37
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,480
I talked him through his breakup.

38
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:36,640
It's really nice to be good friends again.

39
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,520
Are you kidding me?

40
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:41,980
Pam and Jim are totally hooking up.

41
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:43,640
All they do is smile.

42
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:46,560
They're just keeping it a secret, right?

43
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,560
I don't know.

44
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:50,120
There is no evidence of intimacy.

45
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,640
They've been in remarkably good moods.

46
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,080
Could be other things.

47
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,840
Are you kidding me?

48
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,280
And Sunday I'm thinking of going to that flea market at the drive-in.

49
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,280
Well that sounds fun.

50
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:03,480
I'm mountain biking on Sunday and Montage Mountain.

51
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:04,480
Cool.

52
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:05,480
Yeah.

53
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:06,480
Well have fun with that.

54
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:19,200
Ladies and gentlemen, I have some bad news.

55
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,680
Meredith was hit by a car.

56
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,680
What?

57
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,680
Oh man.

58
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,640
It happened this morning in the parking lot.

59
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:29,620
I took her to the hospital and the doctors tried to save her life.

60
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:34,800
They did the best that they could and she is going to be okay.

61
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,360
What is wrong with you?

62
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,880
Why did you have to phrase it like that?

63
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,720
So she's really going to be fine?

64
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,040
Yes.

65
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:47,720
She has a slight pelvic fracture but people have survived far worse.

66
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,880
Thank god you were there.

67
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,880
Yeah.

68
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:54,080
Did you see who did it?

69
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,080
No need.

70
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,440
We can just check the security tapes.

71
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,320
Kind of a good news, bad news there.

72
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:06,160
I was able to be on the scene so quickly because I was in the car that hit her.

73
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,160
